EXPOSE — How to Find the Port
Method 1 — Look at the Code Directly
In your ShopVerse main.go:
goport := os.Getenv("PORT")
if port == "" {
    port = "8080"        // ← DEFAULT PORT IS RIGHT HERE!
}
log.Fatal(app.Listen(":" + port))
//                    ^^^^
//                    app listens on this port
You see 8080 as default → EXPOSE 8080

Method 2 — README
markdown## Run locally
go run ./cmd/main.go
# Backend: http://localhost:8080   ← PORT IS HERE

Method 3 — Existing config files
yaml# docker-compose.yml
ports:
  - "8080:8080"    # ← port is here

# kubernetes service yaml
port: 8080         # ← port is here
targetPort: 8080

